<task id="SPE-080" project="SDAP SPE Admin App">
  <metadata>
    <title>eDiscovery Read-Only Dashboard</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4h</estimated-effort>
    <tags>code-page, frontend, bff-api, phase-3</tags>
    <phase>phase-3</phase>
    <dependencies>SPE-072</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Implement eDiscovery endpoints and a read-only dashboard UI that surfaces eDiscovery cases, custodians, data sources, and review sets relevant to the SharePoint Embedded environment. This provides administrators with compliance visibility without requiring them to navigate to the Microsoft Purview compliance portal.</prompt>
  <role>Full-Stack Developer with Microsoft Graph eDiscovery API and Fluent UI v9 expertise</role>
  <goal>Working BFF endpoints for eDiscovery data and a read-only dashboard page with grids for cases, custodians, data sources, and review sets.</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Use Minimal API endpoint pattern — no controllers</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Use endpoint filters for authorization — no global middleware</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">Do not leak Graph SDK types above the service facade</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Use UniversalDatasetGrid from @spaarke/ui-components shared library</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">All UI must use Fluent UI v9 exclusively — no hard-coded colors, dark mode required</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <context>
    <background>eDiscovery is a compliance feature that enables legal teams to find, hold, and export content for litigation or investigations. The Microsoft Graph eDiscovery API provides access to cases (investigations), custodians (people of interest), data sources (mailboxes, sites, containers), and review sets (curated collections for review). The admin dashboard provides a read-only view of this data so SPE administrators can see what eDiscovery activity relates to their containers.</background>
  </context>
  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="define-dtos">Define DTOs for eDiscovery cases, custodians, data sources, and review sets</step>
    <step order="2" name="add-graph-methods">Add eDiscovery methods to SpeAdminGraphService: ListCasesAsync, GetCaseCustodiansAsync, GetCaseDataSourcesAsync, GetCaseReviewSetsAsync</step>
    <step order="3" name="add-endpoints">Add GET endpoints: /api/spe/ediscovery/cases, /api/spe/ediscovery/cases/{caseId}/custodians, /api/spe/ediscovery/cases/{caseId}/datasources, /api/spe/ediscovery/cases/{caseId}/reviewsets</step>
    <step order="4" name="apply-auth-filter">Apply SpeAdminAuthFilter to all endpoints</step>
    <step order="5" name="create-page">Create components/ediscovery/eDiscoveryPage.tsx with case list and detail view</step>
    <step order="6" name="add-case-detail">Add case detail with tabs for custodians, data sources, and review sets grids</step>
    <step order="7" name="add-navigation-route">Register eDiscoveryPage in app shell navigation/routing</step>
    <step order="8" name="add-tests">Write unit tests for all new endpoints</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/SpeAdmin/Models/EDiscoveryDtos.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/SpeAdmin/SpeAdminGraphService.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Features/SpeAdmin/SpeAdminEndpoints.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/code-pages/spe-admin/src/components/ediscovery/eDiscoveryPage.tsx</output>
    <output type="code">tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Features/SpeAdmin/EDiscoveryEndpointTests.cs</output>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">GET /api/spe/ediscovery/cases returns list of eDiscovery cases</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Case detail endpoints return custodians, data sources, and review sets</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">eDiscoveryPage renders case list with click-to-detail navigation</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Case detail shows tabs for custodians, data sources, and review sets</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All data is read-only — no create/update/delete actions</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SpeAdminAuthFilter is applied to all endpoints</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All UI uses Fluent v9 tokens — no hard-coded colors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Dark mode renders correctly</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit tests pass for all endpoints</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
